fields.description:
When using an invalid format for the volume ID with euca-delete-volume, no error returns.

{code}
[root@viking-01 ~]# euca-delete-volume vol-8888888
[root@viking-01 ~]#
{code}

Based upon AWS, we should return with an error message:

{code}
$ ec2-delete-volume vol-8888888
Client.InvalidParameterValue: Value (vol-8888888) for parameter volume is invalid. Expected: 'vol-...'.
{code}

*Reference*

* http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/api-error-codes.html ( see InvalidParameterValue )

comments.body:
This is fixed in 4.0 as part of EUCA-8501.

{code}
# euca-delete-volume vol-8888888
euca-delete-volume: error (InvalidParameterValue): Value (vol-8888888) for parameter volume is invalid. Expected: 'vol-...'.
{code}
